%% CodeFlare Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / kubectl
    participant API as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant MutWH as Mutating Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant ValWH as Validating Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Ctrl as RayCluster Controller<br/>(reconcile loop)
    participant RouteAPI as OpenShift Route API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Browser as User Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant OAuth as oauth-proxy sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant RayHead as Ray Head Pod<br/>8265/TCP HTTP
    participant RayClient as Ray Client
    participant RayHeadMTLS as Ray Head Service<br/>10001/TCP mTLS

    Note over User, RouteAPI: Flow 1: RayCluster Creation on OpenShift

    User->>API: POST RayCluster CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / kubeconfig
    API->>MutWH: AdmissionReview (mutate)<br/>TLS, API Server CA
    Note right of MutWH: Injects oauth-proxy sidecar<br/>Injects mTLS init containers<br/>Adds volumes & env vars
    MutWH-->>API: Mutated RayCluster spec
    API->>ValWH: AdmissionReview (validate)<br/>TLS, API Server CA
    Note right of ValWH: Validates injected containers<br/>not modified by user
    ValWH-->>API: Admission allowed
    API-->>User: RayCluster created

    Note over Ctrl, RouteAPI: Controller Reconciliation

    Ctrl->>API: Watch RayCluster events<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    API-->>Ctrl: RayCluster created event
    Ctrl->>API: Create ServiceAccount<br/>{cluster}-oauth-proxy
    Ctrl->>API: Create ClusterRoleBinding<br/>system:auth-delegator
    Ctrl->>API: Create Secret<br/>{cluster}-oauth-config (cookie secret)
    Ctrl->>API: Create Secret<br/>ca-secret-{cluster} (self-signed CA)
    Ctrl->>API: Create Service<br/>{cluster}-oauth (443 -> 8443)
    Ctrl->>API: Create NetworkPolicy<br/>{cluster}-head, {cluster}-workers
    Ctrl->>RouteAPI: Create Route<br/>ray-dashboard-{cluster} (reencrypt)
    Ctrl->>RouteAPI: Create Route<br/>rayclient-{cluster} (passthrough)

    Note over Browser, RayHead: Flow 2: Ray Dashboard Access (OpenShift)

    Browser->>Router: GET https://ray-dashboard-{cluster}...<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Router->>OAuth: Forward request<br/>HTTPS TLS (reencrypt)
    Note right of OAuth: OAuth proxy redirects to<br/>OpenShift login if no cookie
    OAuth->>API: SubjectAccessReview<br/>"get pods" in namespace
    API-->>OAuth: Auth result
    OAuth->>RayHead: GET http://localhost:8265<br/>HTTP (localhost, no encryption)
    RayHead-->>OAuth: Dashboard HTML
    OAuth-->>Router: Response
    Router-->>Browser: Ray Dashboard

    Note over RayClient, RayHeadMTLS: Flow 3: Ray Client mTLS Connection

    RayClient->>Router: gRPC connect<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, mTLS client cert
    Router->>RayHeadMTLS: TLS passthrough<br/>10001/TCP mTLS
    Note right of RayHeadMTLS: Verifies client cert<br/>signed by cluster CA
    RayHeadMTLS-->>Router: gRPC response (mTLS)
    Router-->>RayClient: Response
